   "source": [
    "# Geometric Transformations Of Image"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "70d4b664-b7ac-4f05-8114-83d266bd9883",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Affine Transformation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "52239a11-adf1-4c84-a944-2728decf7b39",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "All parallel liness in original image will still be parallel in output image.\n",
    "To find transformation matrix, we need 3 points from input image and their corresponding locations in output image.\n",
    "Then cv2.getAffine transform will create 2X3 matrix which is to be passed to cv.warpAffine."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "798ab951-ed98-48d7-93d0-2f1716a56ea4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. Perspective Transformation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fdc0e934-03bb-4c3a-8bb8-13a56b7624fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You need a 3X3 transformation matrix. Straight lines will remain strainght even after the transformation.\n",
    "You need 4 pts on input image and corresponding points on output image.\n",
    "Among these 4 pts, 3 of them should not be collinear.\n",
    "Then the transformation matrix can be found by function cv2.getPerspective Transform.\n",
    "Then apply cv.warpPerspective with 3X3 transformation matrix."
   ]
  },
  {
